MICHAEL: This is a
hard environment.

26:45.638 --> 26:47.438
The darkness, the cold.

26:47.473 --> 26:49.974
I don't try to play
tough guy in Alaska.

26:55.314 --> 26:56.580
All right.

26:56.616 --> 26:58.916
The winds have died down.
The sun's peeking out.

26:58.951 --> 27:00.284
It's nice and cold.

27:00.319 --> 27:03.120
It's a good time to
move some heavy stuff.

27:08.160 --> 27:11.095
This was originally a
big tangled mess over
my five-mile loop.

27:11.130 --> 27:13.063
But in the end, after
all that hard work,

27:13.099 --> 27:16.367
I'm gonna come out of
here with a bunch of lumber,

27:16.402 --> 27:18.469
and some firewood.

27:18.504 --> 27:22.706
And so now, I'm gonna
take my time and haul
one piece at a time.

27:23.943 --> 27:25.242
(barking).

27:25.277 --> 27:26.543
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

27:26.579 --> 27:28.812
These dogs don't
give me much time to
do anything, really.

27:28.848 --> 27:31.315
They're just knuckleheads
this time of the year.

27:31.350 --> 27:34.051
Hey! Line up!
Come on! Line up!

27:34.086 --> 27:35.786
Super hardheaded breed.

27:35.821 --> 27:38.188
Hard workers and
hardheaded as well.

