Haw! Haw!
Good boys.

28:54.300 --> 28:56.834
This is the best time
of the year in Alaska.

28:58.537 --> 29:02.973
It's cold, it's brutal, and
these dogs motivate you to

29:03.008 --> 29:05.209
get out here, get
the blood pumpin'.

29:05.244 --> 29:09.113
They really do help me cope
with the dark and the cold.

29:09.148 --> 29:11.115
I can't sit around idle.

29:11.150 --> 29:14.051
They have to work.
It's their season.

29:20.392 --> 29:22.793
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

29:22.828 --> 29:26.663
(barking).

29:28.200 --> 29:29.333
All right.

29:29.368 --> 29:31.335
Look at those slabs of wood.

29:31.370 --> 29:34.571
This color right here,
it's such a comforting color.

29:34.607 --> 29:37.741
It's this warm,
setting of the sun color,

29:37.777 --> 29:40.144
mixed in with wispy clouds.

29:40.179 --> 29:43.614
And so, with that setting sun,
I gotta keep movin',

29:43.649 --> 29:47.451
keep runnin', keep puttin'
them miles on them dogs.

29:47.486 --> 29:50.954
I got two in one shot,
bunch of wood and some
miles on my dogs.

29:50.990 --> 29:53.290
I'm gonna get one more run in.

