So out here, I
like to stay moving.

30:04.436 --> 30:06.303
I don't like to stop,
you know.

30:06.338 --> 30:07.638
There's so much to do.

30:07.673 --> 30:10.941
Just surviving alone will
take up most of your time.

30:18.317 --> 30:19.983
What you smell, Java? Huh?

30:20.019 --> 30:22.686
Oh, yeah. These are all
broken branches.

30:25.491 --> 30:28.325
This one's living too, so.

30:30.029 --> 30:32.896
There's, yeah, you can see
the bear's hair right here.

30:34.400 --> 30:36.200
Yeah.

30:36.235 --> 30:37.768
What he does is he
just comes over here,

30:37.803 --> 30:39.937
and he puts his
back against the tree,

30:39.972 --> 30:41.972
and just kind of
marks his territory,

30:42.007 --> 30:46.176
and any branches that
are in the way just break
or fall on the ground.

30:46.879 --> 30:48.979
It's a good day to be doing a,
a little bit of bear defense

30:49.014 --> 30:51.315
on the cabin, that's for sure.

30:52.284 --> 30:54.484
Come here, Java.
Hey! Come here.

30:54.520 --> 30:58.255
My goal today is to
make a latch for the
door for the cabin.

31:00.326 --> 31:03.427
The purpose of the latch is
to keep Java in the cabin

31:03.462 --> 31:05.329
when it's necessary.

31:05.364 --> 31:08.265
I rarely leave her in there
without myself being in there.

31:08.300 --> 31:12.369
But there are times usually
when there are bears or wolves

31:12.404 --> 31:14.905
roaming that, uh, it's, it's
kind of important to keep her

31:14.940 --> 31:18.208
in there for her own safety.

31:18.244 --> 31:23.981
So I got to find a, a little
spruce tree to cut down.

31:24.016 --> 31:27.684
And that's gonna be, uh,
what goes through the door.

31:27.720 --> 31:30.721
And, um, I'll have a
handle on each end of that.

31:33.158 --> 31:35.759
Let's see, let's see.

31:37.096 --> 31:40.731
God, that's such a, that's
a big (bleep) grizzly bear!

